The paper proposes a novel model for contextual bandits that addresses two major limitations of existing models. The paper focuses on developing a UCB-type policy and proving its regret bounds. The paper's contributions are relevant to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), computational economics (cs.CE), and information theory (cs.IT).
